{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Roy Gould: Less than a year from now,"},{"time":3000,"text":"the world is going to celebrate the International Year of Astronomy,"},{"time":6000,"text":"which marks the 400th anniversary"},{"time":8000,"text":"of Galileo's first glimpse of the night sky through a telescope."},{"time":12000,"text":"In a few months, the world is also going to celebrate"},{"time":15000,"text":"the launch of a new invention from Microsoft Research,"},{"time":20000,"text":"which I think is going to have as profound an impact"},{"time":23000,"text":"on the way we view the universe as Galileo did four centuries ago."},{"time":28000,"text":"It's called the WorldWide Telescope,"},{"time":31000,"text":"and I want to thank TED and Microsoft for allowing me to bring it to your attention."},{"time":36000,"text":"And I want to urge you, when you get a chance,"},{"time":39000,"text":"to give it a closer look at the TED Lab downstairs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"The WorldWide Telescope takes the best images"},{"time":49000,"text":"from the world's greatest telescopes on Earth and in space,"},{"time":54000,"text":"and has woven them seamlessly"},{"time":58000,"text":"to produce a holistic view of the universe."},{"time":66000,"text":"It's going to change the way we do astronomy,"},{"time":68000,"text":"it's going to change the way we teach astronomy"},{"time":71000,"text":"and I think most importantly"},{"time":73000,"text":"it's going to change the way we see ourselves in the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77000,"text":"If we were having this TED meeting in our grandparents' day,"},{"time":80000,"text":"that might not be so big a claim."},{"time":83000,"text":"In 1920, for example, you weren't allowed to drink;"},{"time":86000,"text":"if you were a woman, you weren't allowed to vote;"},{"time":89000,"text":"and if you looked up at the stars and the Milky Way on a summer night,"},{"time":94000,"text":"what you saw was thought to be the entire universe."},{"time":98000,"text":"In fact, the head of Harvard's observatory back then"},{"time":102000,"text":"gave a great debate in which he argued"},{"time":104000,"text":"that the Milky Way Galaxy was the entire universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107000,"text":"Harvard was wrong, big time. (Laughter)"},{"time":109000,"text":"Of course, we know today that galaxies extend far beyond our own galaxy."},{"time":113000,"text":"We can see all the way out to the edge of the observable universe,"},{"time":117000,"text":"all the way back in time,"},{"time":119000,"text":"almost to the moment of the Big Bang itself."},{"time":122000,"text":"We can see across the entire spectrum of light,"},{"time":126000,"text":"revealing worlds that had previously been invisible."},{"time":130000,"text":"We see these magnificent star nurseries,"},{"time":134000,"text":"where nature has somehow arranged for just the right numbers"},{"time":138000,"text":"and just the right sizes of stars to be born for life to arise."},{"time":142000,"text":"We see alien worlds, we see alien solar systems --"},{"time":146000,"text":"300 now, and still counting --"},{"time":149000,"text":"and they're not like us."},{"time":153000,"text":"We see black holes at the heart of our galaxy,"},{"time":156000,"text":"in the Milky Way, and elsewhere in the universe,"},{"time":159000,"text":"where time itself seems to stand still."},{"time":162000,"text":"But until now, our view of the universe has been disconnected and fragmented,"},{"time":168000,"text":"and I think that many of the marvelous stories that nature has to tell us"},{"time":172000,"text":"have fallen through the cracks. And that's changing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175000,"text":"I want to just briefly mention three reasons"},{"time":177000,"text":"why my colleagues and I, in astronomy and in education,"},{"time":181000,"text":"are so excited about the WorldWide Telescope"},{"time":184000,"text":"and why we think it's truly transformative."},{"time":186000,"text":"First, it enables you to experience the universe:"},{"time":191000,"text":"the WorldWide Telescope, for me, is a kind of magic carpet"},{"time":194000,"text":"that lets you navigate through the universe where you want to go."},{"time":199000,"text":"Second: you can tour the universe with astronomers as your guides."},{"time":205000,"text":"And I'm not talking here about just experts who are telling you what you're seeing,"},{"time":210000,"text":"but really people who are passionate about the various nooks and crannies of the universe,"},{"time":216000,"text":"who can share their enthusiasm"},{"time":218000,"text":"and can make the universe a welcoming place."},{"time":220000,"text":"And third, you can create your own tours --"},{"time":224000,"text":"you can share them with friends, you can create them with friends --"},{"time":227000,"text":"and that's the part that I think I'm most excited about"},{"time":229000,"text":"because I think that at heart, we are all storytellers."},{"time":233000,"text":"And in telling stories,"},{"time":235000,"text":"each of us is going to understand the universe in our own way."},{"time":239000,"text":"We're going to have a personal universe."},{"time":242000,"text":"I think we're going to see a community of storytellers evolve and emerge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247000,"text":"Before I introduce the person responsible for the WorldWide Telescope,"},{"time":252000,"text":"I just want to leave you with this brief thought:"},{"time":254000,"text":"when I ask people, \"How does the night sky make you feel?\""},{"time":258000,"text":"they often say, \"Oh, tiny. I feel tiny and insignificant.\""},{"time":262000,"text":"Well, our gaze fills the universe."},{"time":265000,"text":"And thanks to the creators of the WorldWide Telescope,"},{"time":270000,"text":"we can now start to have a dialogue with the universe."},{"time":274000,"text":"I think the WorldWide Telescope will convince you"},{"time":277000,"text":"that we may be tiny, but we are truly, wonderfully significant."},{"time":282000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":284000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":289000,"text":"I can't tell you what a privilege it is"},{"time":292000,"text":"to introduce Curtis Wong from Microsoft. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296000,"text":"Curtis Wong: Thank you, Roy."},{"time":301000,"text":"So, what you're seeing here is a wonderful presentation,"},{"time":304000,"text":"but it's one of the tours."},{"time":306000,"text":"And actually this tour is one that was created earlier."},{"time":309000,"text":"And the tours are all totally interactive,"},{"time":311000,"text":"so that if I were to go somewhere ..."},{"time":313000,"text":"you may be watching a tour and you can pause anywhere along the way,"},{"time":316000,"text":"pull up other information --"},{"time":318000,"text":"there are lots of Web and information sources"},{"time":320000,"text":"about places you might want to go --"},{"time":322000,"text":"you can zoom in, you can pull back out."},{"time":325000,"text":"The whole resources are there available for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327000,"text":"So, Microsoft -- this is a project that -- WorldWide Telescope is dedicated to Jim Gray,"},{"time":334000,"text":"who's our colleague, and a lot of his work that he did"},{"time":337000,"text":"is really what makes this project possible."},{"time":340000,"text":"It's a labor of love for us and our small team,"},{"time":343000,"text":"and we really hope it will inspire kids to explore and learn about the universe."},{"time":347000,"text":"So basically, kids of all ages, like us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"And so WorldWide Telescope will be available this spring."},{"time":352000,"text":"It'll be a free download -- thank you, Craig Mundie --"},{"time":357000,"text":"and it'll be available at the website WorldWideTelescope.org,"},{"time":361000,"text":"which is something new."},{"time":363000,"text":"And so, what you've seen today"},{"time":366000,"text":"is less than a fraction of one percent of what is in here,"},{"time":370000,"text":"and in the TED Lab, we have a tour"},{"time":372000,"text":"that was created by a six-year-old named Benjamin"},{"time":374000,"text":"that will knock your socks off. (Laughter)"},{"time":376000,"text":"So we'll see you there. Thank you."},{"time":380000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}